#: original_texis/cmdargs.texi:103
msgid "When Emacs starts up, it displays the startup buffer in one window, and the buffer visiting @var{file} in another window (@pxref{Windows}).  If you supply more than one file argument, the displayed file is the last one specified on the command line; the other files are visited but their buffers are not shown."
