#. type: table
#: original_texis/cmdargs.texi:112
msgid "If the startup buffer is disabled (@pxref{Entering Emacs}), then starting Emacs with one file argument displays the buffer visiting @var{file} in a single window.  With two file arguments, Emacs displays the files in two different windows.  With more than two file arguments, Emacs displays the last file specified in one window, plus another window with a Buffer Menu showing all the other files (@pxref{Several Buffers}).  To inhibit using the Buffer Menu for this, change the variable @code{inhibit-startup-buffer-menu} to @code{t}."
