msgid "An Emacs frame has an internal border and an outer border.  The internal border is an extra strip of the background color around the text portion of the frame.  Emacs itself draws the internal border.  The outer border is drawn by X outside the tool and menu bars of the frame.  There is also an external border which is drawn by the window manager.  The size of the external border cannot be set from within Emacs."
